<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-283-078  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 283 078.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  March 15 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ATandamp;T updates C++ language system. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Product:   C++ Language System 2.1 (Program development software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersProduct IntroductionProgram Development ToolsSoftware engineeringSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ATandamp;T UPDATES C++ LANGUAGE SYSTEM MORRISTOWN, NEW JERSEY, U.S.A., 1990 MAR 12(NB) -- ATandamp;T's Unix Software Operation (USO) today announced that a newversion of its C++ Language System, Release 2.1, will be available at the endof March.andP;  The new release contains fixes for minor bugs detected bydevelopers and customers since the release of Version 2.0 last June.andM;The C++ language adds object-oriented programming capabilities to the Clanguage while continuing to support the traditional procedural methods ofprogramming.andP;  &quot;This product delivers on the promise we made to provideincreased robustness for our C++ Language System product,&quot; said Mike DeFazio,director of system software at the ATandamp;T Unix Software Operation.andP;  &quot;Release2.1 also demonstrates USO's intent to provide the reference implementation ofthe language as defined by its author, Dr. Bjarne Stroustrup of ATandamp;T BellLaboratories.&quot;andM;The C++ Language System Release 2.1 is available to software vendors as a newproduct in source code form for $25,000 while those who previously licensedRelease 2.0 may upgrade all their processors for a one-time fee of $5,000.andO;Vendors who acquire Release 2.1 may distribute binary versions on a no-feeupgrade to customers who have purchased their C++ product based on Release2.0.andP;  Vendors wishing to license the C++ Language System Release 2.1 maycontact one of the following UnIX Software Operation offices --Greensboro,N.C (1-800-828-UNIX), London (+44-1-567-7711), Tokyo (+81-3-431- 3670) or NewDelhi (+91-11-331-0513).andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/19900314/Press Contact: Dick Muldoon,ATandamp;T, 201-829-7212)</TEXT></DOC>